Secondly, the interaction of the CDs with free PEI in the none-silica matrix system was studied by the fluorescence spectra of CDs. As shown in Fig. 4
                         (curve a) and Fig. 5
                        A, after mixing 60 μL of free-state PEI (40.0 mg mL−1) and 50 μL of CDs solution inside the water droplet of the reverse microemulsion system without adding the TEOS, either the fluorescence intensities or the fluorescence spectra of CDs almost unchanged as their mixing time increasing from 0.5 to 30 h. This result indicated that the free-state PEI did not react with CDs in the water droplet of the TEOS-free reverse microemulsion system;
